## Master plan (navigate via digest, open full source when needed)

**Digest (read this at boot):** `axhy-cognitive-system/docs/book/digests/MASTER_PLAN_DIGEST.md` — ~2,000-token navigation summary covering product, personas, architecture, hard rules, iteration locks, data model truths, current build status, and key constraints. Authority level: digest (navigation, not source of truth).

**Full source (open only when needed):** `/Users/thotaakshay/.claude/plans/now-i-think-it-functional-kernighan.md` — the 60K-word context document. Open it when:
- Implementing a locked iteration (need full decision details from §G)
- Answering founder questions about open questions (§H)
- Changing pricing, onboarding, AI boundaries, data model, or retention rules
- Modifying persona workflows (supervisor, worker, HR, admin)
- Making decisions that depend on omitted sections (schemas, marketing, contingency)
- Digest and impactCheck results disagree (full source resolves conflicts)
- Digest `source_hash` does not match current master plan hash (digest is stale)

**For all other tasks:** use `impactCheck("plain English description of task")` to surface relevant master plan content from the brain on demand.

